  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <div class="faq">
    <h3>How do I respond to Google reviews?</h3>
    <p>Go to your Google Business Profile, find the review, click Reply, write your response and click Post. Always respond within 24 hours, thank the reviewer, and address their specific feedback.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="faq">
    <h3>Should I respond to all Google reviews?</h3>
    <p>Yes. Responding to all reviews signals to Google that your business is actively managed, which improves your local SEO ranking.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="faq">
    <h3>How long should a Google review response be?</h3>
    <p>Between 50 and 150 words is ideal. Long enough to be genuine and include natural keywords, short enough to be readable.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="faq" style="border:none">
    <h3>Can I delete a Google review response?</h3>
    <p>Yes. Go to your Google Business Profile, find your response, and click Edit or Delete. You can update or remove your response at any time.</p>
  </div>
